Vice President Biden met with Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos and a group of bipartisan US Senators to discuss the progress of the Colombian government's peace talks with the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia. They discussed the necessary elements for a sustainable peace, including justice for victims, demobilization and reintegration of combatants, extension of the rule of law and government services, and creating education, jobs, and economic opportunities for Colombia. They also agreed on the importance of working with the US Congress to ensure continued bipartisan support for Colombia after the peace accords are signed.